{
  "stem": "13469.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But one way or another, neither me nor [INAUDIBLE] two years later had their bar mitzvah in Holland.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We had it afterwards, after the war, in England.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So whether we were aware of it at that time, I'm not quite sure.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What else should I say about Amsterdam?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Basically, things just got worse, and more and more people were deported, and eventually, it was our turn.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In 1943, there were very big raids, and in our case, it was the 20th of June, 1943.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were two very big raids-- [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] as they call them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I'm not sure if that's a Dutch word or a German word or an English word-- [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was basically roundups.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They cordoned off the whole of the south Amsterdam area where all the Jews, especially all the German refugee Jews, lived.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was cordoned off by military vehicles and tanks and all this sort of thing, and the German army and Dutch army and police, et cetera, very early in the morning, because before the curfew finished on  the Sunday morning, before 6 o'clock in the morning, when Jews were not allowed out.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So all Jews had to be in their home or were supposed to be in their home.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so they cordoned it, off and nobody could get in or out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They wouldn't let Dutch people in or out either.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Everything was just shut off completely.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the SS or Gestapo or whoever it was came around to all the doors.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There were loudspeakers going around saying all Jews come out with their luggage for resettlement, deportation.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And individual officers came around to all our addresses because the [INAUDIBLE] had a list of all Jews and the addresses where all the Jews lived in Amsterdam.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
